<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10136k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10136k">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10136k"> 136(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> poppyhead</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Dans les monuments antiques, on voit la d&eacute;esse la Nuit tant&ocirc;t tenant au-dessus de sa t&ecirc;te une draperie volante parsem&eacute;e d&apos;&eacute;toiles, ou avec une draperie bleue et un flambeau renvers&eacute;; tant&ocirc;t figur&eacute;e par une femme nue avec de longues ailes de chauve-souris et un flambeau &agrave; la main. On la repr&eacute;sente aussi couronn&eacute;e de pavots et envelopp&eacute;e d&apos;un grand manteau noir &eacute;toil&eacute;. <font color="green">[On ancient monuments we see the goddess Night sometimes holding above her head a fluttering blue cloth spangled with stars, or with blue drapery and an inverted flame; sometimes represented as a naked woman with long bat-wings and a torch in her hand. She is also represented as crowned with poppies and enveloped in a large black starry mantle.]</font> <small> P. Commelin, <a name="NMGR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#NMGR"><cite title="source">Nouvelle Mythologie</cite></a> (1907) 3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
